description:
You are a digital archivist creating an exhibit on 'The Birth of the Modern Web'. Using the Internet Archive's Wayback Machine (https://web.archive.org), find the earliest available archived snapshot for google.com, amazon.com, wikipedia.org, youtube.com, and twitter.com. Bookmark each snapshot in a Firefox folder named 'Web Archive Research' and create a JSON report at ~/Documents/web_history_report.json containing the earliest capture date, Wayback URL, and a brief description for each site.

The JSON report should follow this structure for all five websites:
{
  "google.com": {
    "earliest_capture_date": "YYYY-MM-DD",
    "wayback_url": "https://web.archive.org/web/...",
    "description": "Brief description of the page content"
  },
  ...
}
